  "accordion": [
    {
      "trigger": "What is SuperCSS?",
      "content": "SuperCSS is a token-driven CSS design system. Every component consumes <code>--sc-*</code> custom properties so themes, palettes, and density scales mutate the visual output without touching markup."
    },
    {
      "trigger": "How does theming work?",
      "content": "Set <code>data-theme</code>, <code>data-palette</code>, <code>data-mode</code>, <code>data-density</code>, or <code>data-radius</code> on the <code>html</code> element. The mixer layer rewrites the token values and every component updates instantly."
    },
    {
      "trigger": "Can I use this with React or Vue?",
      "content": "Yes. SuperCSS is framework-agnostic CSS. The Angular template is one port — the same class contracts work in React, Vue, Svelte, or plain HTML. Only the state wiring changes per framework."
    }
